
Requirements
============

- Python 2.3 or higher (not Python 3.x).
You can get the latest stable Python distribution from here:
http://www.python.org/download/


Manual installation
===================

If you have downloaded a pyftpdlib package, follow the following steps:

- Unpack it:

> tar zxf pyftpdlib-0.3.0.tar.gz

- Change to the pyftpdlib directory:

> cd pyftpdlib

- Run setup.py to install pyftpdlib. This step need to be run as root.

> python setup.py install

Note: Windows users just need to run:

> setup.py install


Using easy_install
==================

If you have easy_install [1] on your system, installing pyftpdlib is quite
simple. Just run:

> easy_install.py pyftpdlib

This will get the most updated pyftpdlib from the Python pypi repository [2],
unpack it and install it automatically.

Note: if you already have an old version of pyftpdlib installed, easy_install
will not automatically download the latest version.
You can ask for a particular version by running for example:

> easy_install pyftpdlib==0.3.0



References:
[1] easy_install: http://peak.telecommunity.com/DevCenter/EasyInstall
[2] pypi: http://pypi.python.org/pypi